:{{see|pictor}}

==English==
===Etymology===
Named by the French [[astronomer]] Nicolas Louis de Lacaille in 1763. From {{L.}} ''[[pictor]]'', an "easel"
===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia|Pictor}}
'''Pictor'''

#{{constellation}}: A [[summer]] [[constellation]] of the [[southern]] sky, said to resemble an [[easel]]. It lies between the constellations [[Carina]] and [[Dorado]].

